cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on visual traffic surveillance, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses camera calibration, which is a crucial part of robotics and autonomous systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data set, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia data (videos), which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of GPS data, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
